    "note": "Archetype A dyad: participants={ASIA-CHINA}, primary_target=OCEANIA-AUSTRALIA. The target gate is the AND-substitute, so generic domain nouns (quota, tariff, export) are safe -- a title only attributes if it also carries Australia. No country names. `economic coercion`/`weaponisation` deliberately EXCLUDED: stance vocabulary belongs in narratives_v2.framing_keywords, not the topic gate (vocab spec rule 5). Corporate anchors (BHP/Fortescue/CMRG) are included because the dyad gate makes them the iron-ore dispute rather than global commercial noise -- audit them. | RULE 6b PRUNE (post-audit): dropped short Latin-script non-EN aliases that substring-collide with English text -- `vin`(fr) matched Kevin/driving/savings, `litio`(es,it) matched Coalition, and `quota`(fr,it) duplicated the EN entry (Latin-collapse rule). orge/orzo/vino/Zoll/Wein dropped as the same latent class. The corpus is 94% EN so these cost nothing in recall."
